The paper discusses reasoning in the OWL 2 Full ontology language, which is a language for the Semantic Web. This suggests that the paper is likely to be related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The use of automated theorem proving systems also suggests a connection to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper's focus on ontology languages and reasoning may also make it relevant to database systems (cs.DB).
